1
00:00:07,226 --> 00:00:09,328
This town seems to
have a lot of nice stalls.

2
00:00:10,009 --> 00:00:10,449
Agreed.

3
00:00:10,549 --> 00:00:12,189
Might be worth doing some looking around.

4
00:00:16,034 --> 00:00:18,637
Mere paces in and this
place is clearly full of life.

5
00:00:18,777 --> 00:00:20,499
You can tell by the number of bars.

6
00:00:20,839 --> 00:00:21,980
You've worked so hard.

7
00:00:22,540 --> 00:00:24,302
May I take you shopping to say thanks?

8
00:00:25,723 --> 00:00:27,945
This town seems to
have a lot of nice stalls.

9
00:00:29,107 --> 00:00:30,288
If you want to, I suppose.

10
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:35,971
What are you doing, Frieren?

11
00:00:36,291 --> 00:00:37,291
Let's get a move on!

12
00:02:17,990 --> 00:02:19,811
What do you gain by being so rude?

13
00:02:20,312 --> 00:02:22,333
You berate me every single chance you get!

14
00:02:22,753 --> 00:02:24,755
If you hate me, just come
out and say it already!

15
00:02:25,855 --> 00:02:27,152
I'm going back to my master!

16
00:02:31,476 --> 00:02:34,262
Would it kill her to listen to what I have to say
once in a while before she—????!

17
00:02:36,883 --> 00:02:38,124
What's all the noise about?

18
00:02:38,624 --> 00:02:39,624
Lovebirds fighting?

19
00:02:41,663 --> 00:02:43,945
If you weren't aware,
today is Fern's birthday.

20
00:02:44,526 --> 00:02:47,068
And unfortunately, Stark
forgot to get her a gift.

21
00:02:47,869 --> 00:02:48,990
She's not taking it well.

22
00:02:52,353 --> 00:02:54,795
If you ask me, you were
a bit too harsh this time.

23
00:02:55,696 --> 00:02:58,438
You never listen to a single
thing that poor lad has to say.

24
00:03:01,261 --> 00:03:03,283
To be honest, I didn't
get you anything either.

25
00:03:04,248 --> 00:03:07,629
When it comes to us men, we couldn't
care less about trivial dates, you know.

26
00:03:07,990 --> 00:03:11,431
Anniversaries, birthdays... That hurt!

27
00:03:11,831 --> 00:03:12,331
I get it!

28
00:03:12,511 --> 00:03:15,172
Okay, I'll go pick up a trinket
for your birthday if you'll stop!

29
00:03:15,753 --> 00:03:16,913
At least spare my knees!

30
00:03:22,275 --> 00:03:25,197
After that beating, I feel
even more sorry for him.

31
00:03:25,837 --> 00:03:29,218
I'm old enough now not to make a
big stink if somebody hurts my feelings.

32
00:03:29,378 --> 00:03:33,720
But a girl like you has the power to stir up
the emotions of a boy like him into a whirlwind.

33
00:03:40,144 --> 00:03:41,946
My advice is to go after the kid.

34
00:03:47,370 --> 00:03:48,832
That might be my advice too.

35
00:04:21,919 --> 00:04:24,361
I think her hair ornament
has a butterfly on it, too.

36
00:04:26,562 --> 00:04:27,983
A cute pouch you've got there.

37
00:04:28,764 --> 00:04:29,764
You don't like it?

38
00:04:30,065 --> 00:04:33,027
I don't like how used to keeping
the company of women you seem.

39
00:04:33,787 --> 00:04:34,787
Of course.

40
00:04:36,009 --> 00:04:37,450
So, did you ever find Stark?

41
00:04:38,611 --> 00:04:40,512
I spotted him in the plaza.

42
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:43,233
Couldn't bring yourself
to talk to him, could you?

43
00:04:45,956 --> 00:04:46,956
I understand.

44
00:04:47,197 --> 00:04:48,677
It's not that you don't like the guy.

45
00:04:49,295 --> 00:04:52,076
You just aren't used to keeping
the company of men your own age.

46
00:04:53,116 --> 00:04:54,116
Oh, to be young.

47
00:04:55,137 --> 00:04:55,557
No matter.

48
00:04:56,077 --> 00:04:57,077
Choose whatever you want.

49
00:04:58,038 --> 00:04:59,798
We can take a look at
some other shops, too.

50
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,961
Thanks, but that's quite alright.

51
00:05:07,542 --> 00:05:09,422
Fine, guess I'll choose on my own.

52
00:05:10,883 --> 00:05:14,184
Anyway, if he did forget to get you
something, don't take it personally.

53
00:05:14,904 --> 00:05:17,025
He doesn't strike me as
the conscientious type.

54
00:05:17,948 --> 00:05:20,609
I doubt there are many years he
even remembers his own birthday.

55
00:05:21,269 --> 00:05:22,269
Don't blame the fool.

56
00:05:23,729 --> 00:05:26,730
He didn't have to remember
because I gave him a present on it.

57
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,070
Right.

58
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:29,991
You picked out one together, didn't you?

59
00:05:30,671 --> 00:05:31,671
How did you know that?

60
00:05:32,911 --> 00:05:36,152
Most people wouldn't decline when someone
offers to buy them whatever they want.

61
00:05:37,232 --> 00:05:40,493
You must already have some birthday
shopping memory you consider sacred.

62
00:05:40,993 --> 00:05:42,253
That's why you told me no.

63
00:05:43,974 --> 00:05:44,974
I guess that could be.

64
00:05:45,742 --> 00:05:48,422
I don't know about Sacred,
but it did feel like the right choice.

65
00:05:49,443 --> 00:05:50,443
I believe it.

66
00:05:51,403 --> 00:05:55,304
Now, apologize to Stark, then you two
can pick out the best president in town.

67
00:05:58,224 --> 00:06:01,745
Sure, he's slow on the
uptake, but he's just a kid.

68
00:06:04,025 --> 00:06:05,445
You want to make up with him, yes?

69
00:06:06,806 --> 00:06:09,666
Remember that people can't
know how you feel until you tell them.

70
00:06:13,387 --> 00:06:14,387
Guess you're right.

71
00:06:15,397 --> 00:06:16,797
I'm gonna head back to the inn now.

72
00:06:16,897 --> 00:06:17,897
One thing.

73
00:06:18,558 --> 00:06:26,440
I'm sorry about all the kicking.

74
00:06:37,524 --> 00:06:38,524
Mr. Stark.

75
00:06:43,606 --> 00:06:44,606
Fern...

76
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:51,021
I...

77
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:52,161
Sorry!

78
00:06:55,565 --> 00:06:58,106
I wanted to choose a gift with
you to make sure you'd love it.

79
00:06:58,667 --> 00:07:02,757
But after you got upset, I didn't want it to look
like I was trying to dig myself out of a hole.

80
00:07:02,781 --> 00:07:03,771
So I didn't say anything.

81
00:07:05,192 --> 00:07:09,155
Because I got nervous and I was worried
you might become even more mad at me.

82
00:07:11,096 --> 00:07:13,016
That wouldn't have made
me mad in the slightest.

83
00:07:14,098 --> 00:07:16,916
Mr. Stark, would you forgive me?

84
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:19,002
I was too harsh with you.

85
00:07:21,797 --> 00:07:22,797
Please.

86
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:23,998
I've grown used to it.

87
00:07:24,999 --> 00:07:26,339
I really am sorry, though.

88
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:30,541
You ready to shop?

89
00:07:33,863 --> 00:07:41,863
Yeah.

90
00:07:48,531 --> 00:07:49,872
Spying on the sweethearts?

91
00:07:50,701 --> 00:07:52,022
That's in poor taste, Frieren.

92
00:07:52,742 --> 00:07:53,823
You're doing the same.

93
00:07:55,924 --> 00:07:57,205
I'm just glad that they made up.

94
00:08:00,767 --> 00:08:06,791
The older you get, the better you start understanding relationships,
and the better you can do that, the fewer conflicts arise.

95
00:08:09,613 --> 00:08:11,734
Arguments like that are
a privilege of the young.

96
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:14,956
This can't have been easy for you, Frieren.

97
00:08:15,737 --> 00:08:17,478
Looking after two kids all alone.

98
00:08:20,047 --> 00:08:21,668
You understand relationships?

99
00:08:21,969 --> 00:08:23,210
Make that three kids.

100
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:30,736
It struck me as odd Fern turned
to me for advice instead of you.

101
00:08:31,817 --> 00:08:35,440
A girl wouldn't do that unless she has
someone in her past she's comparing me to.

102
00:08:36,821 --> 00:08:39,443
You do know Fern was
raised by Heiter, don't you?

103
00:08:39,904 --> 00:08:42,002
That's the last person I
should be compared to.

104
00:08:42,026 --> 00:08:43,587
He was a great priest.

105
00:08:44,109 --> 00:08:46,010
Great isn't the word I would use.

106
00:08:46,691 --> 00:08:49,233
When he wasn't drunk,
he was deathly hungover.

107
00:08:49,653 --> 00:08:50,894
He's gone undead on us.

108
00:08:51,454 --> 00:08:53,252
He was terribly picky with his food.

109
00:08:53,276 --> 00:08:54,356
Quit it, Heiter.

110
00:08:54,657 --> 00:08:56,218
And he lied more often than not.

111
00:08:56,498 --> 00:08:58,039
I haven't had a drop all day.

112
00:08:59,060 --> 00:09:01,041
He was a corrupt priest, plain and simple.

113
00:09:01,842 --> 00:09:04,443
Though I admit, your
depravity far exceeds his.

114
00:09:04,924 --> 00:09:06,025
Yeah, sorry about that.

115
00:09:07,846 --> 00:09:09,287
All that stuff is hard to believe.

116
00:09:09,952 --> 00:09:11,793
Sounds nothing like the Heiter I remember.

117
00:09:12,013 --> 00:09:14,474
He was a kind, dependable,
and upright old man.

118
00:09:15,394 --> 00:09:16,394
A proper grown-up.

119
00:09:16,875 --> 00:09:18,516
The very opposite of what I've become.

120
00:09:21,797 --> 00:09:23,438
The years have changed you, Heiter.

121
00:09:23,958 --> 00:09:25,019
You've grown dignified.

122
00:09:27,180 --> 00:09:30,061
To me, that sounds like
a nice way of saying old.

123
00:09:30,981 --> 00:09:33,983
A certain level of maturity
comes naturally as we age.

124
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:38,073
Or rather, that's what I wish I could say.

125
00:09:38,494 --> 00:09:43,560
Truth is, though my body has grown and shrunk,
my mind has hardly changed since I was a child.

126
00:09:44,141 --> 00:09:46,224
I've pretended to be an adult all my life.

127
00:09:46,725 --> 00:09:50,870
Though I might look the part now, not
a bit of adulthood has stirred within me.

128
00:09:51,968 --> 00:09:56,110
I'd like to be a proper grown-up,
but I fear I'll pretend until I die.

129
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:59,051
It's important that children have adults.

130
00:09:59,391 --> 00:10:02,273
Little ones can't thrive
without emotional support.

131
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:04,994
Fern is the hard-working sort.

132
00:10:05,414 --> 00:10:08,835
She needs a lot of
guidance and a lot of praise.

133
00:10:09,596 --> 00:10:13,057
If you're still a child, then shouldn't
you be praised for maintaining this ruse?

134
00:10:13,337 --> 00:10:14,838
Where's the grown-up to praise you?

135
00:10:16,279 --> 00:10:19,080
She's up above somewhere
waiting for me to join her.

136
00:10:20,396 --> 00:10:23,379
I'll have to venture into heaven
before I receive my reward.

137
00:10:24,060 --> 00:10:26,442
Well, while you're still here,
I could always praise you.

138
00:10:28,124 --> 00:10:29,285
You'd do that for me?

139
00:10:29,886 --> 00:10:30,486
How kind.

140
00:10:30,847 --> 00:10:34,590
But I doubt you understand just how
a withering human like me might feel.

141
00:10:35,331 --> 00:10:36,973
So how do you intend to praise me?

142
00:10:49,096 --> 00:10:51,917
I must admit that was
much nicer than I expected.

143
00:10:52,937 --> 00:10:57,999
Frieren, once I get to Heaven, I'll
have a word with the Goddess for you.

144
00:10:58,899 --> 00:11:02,437
When you join me, you should
be praised by her too, my friend.

145
00:11:02,461 --> 00:11:03,461
Oh?

146
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:05,722
Then I'll look forward to it.

147
00:11:12,564 --> 00:11:14,225
What do you think you're doing, Frieren?

148
00:11:15,145 --> 00:11:17,846
In my opinion, you're as
proper as grown-ups come, Sein.

149
00:11:24,004 --> 00:11:25,467
If only you were an older lady.

150
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:27,030
This moment would be perfect.

151
00:11:27,872 --> 00:11:29,174
You should be glad then.

152
00:11:29,956 --> 00:11:31,720
Precious few women are older than me.

153
00:11:41,612 --> 00:11:42,612
Thank you, sir.

154
00:11:43,073 --> 00:11:46,115
This area has an extreme
deficit of passenger carriages.

155
00:11:46,315 --> 00:11:48,717
We must all help our
fellow men in times of need.

156
00:11:49,357 --> 00:11:52,419
I work as a merchant, selling
my wares in the town up ahead.

157
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:55,161
I supply the people there
with fine accessories.

158
00:11:55,802 --> 00:11:57,082
Look at my stock, if you'd like.

159
00:11:57,683 --> 00:11:59,384
You're quite the salesman, aren't you?

160
00:12:00,145 --> 00:12:01,926
Alas, finer things are lost on me.

161
00:12:02,807 --> 00:12:04,728
My apprentice Fern may
be interested, though.

162
00:12:05,508 --> 00:12:06,508
Huh?

163
00:12:06,569 --> 00:12:07,750
Did you buy a new bracelet?

164
00:12:10,090 --> 00:12:12,171
Well, uh, kind of.

165
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:14,873
That's a pretty design.

166
00:12:15,754 --> 00:12:17,715
I have a ring with the
very same pattern on it.

167
00:12:18,756 --> 00:12:20,937
It was a gift from Himmel
for a job well done.

168
00:12:21,698 --> 00:12:23,179
I think it would match perfectly.

169
00:12:23,639 --> 00:12:24,639
I've never seen it.

170
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:26,220
Let me think.

171
00:12:26,401 --> 00:12:27,502
Where did I put that thing?

172
00:12:30,063 --> 00:12:31,063
Under here?

173
00:12:33,866 --> 00:12:36,407
Goodness, you're so disorganized.

174
00:12:38,269 --> 00:12:39,269
Finally.

175
00:12:51,903 --> 00:12:54,065
Sorry, I let my guard down.

176
00:12:55,486 --> 00:12:59,551
Avian monsters are cunning beasts
and very skilled at concealing their mana.

177
00:13:00,552 --> 00:13:01,552
What to do?

178
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:05,832
Let's defeat the monster
and then figure something out.

179
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:08,971
You mages use magic
to fly around all the time.

180
00:13:08,995 --> 00:13:11,977
You can make a carriage
float for a bit, can't you?

181
00:13:12,478 --> 00:13:13,478
Think, Stark.

182
00:13:13,739 --> 00:13:15,740
Have you ever seen a
flying carriage before?

183
00:13:16,041 --> 00:13:17,362
Yeah, we're in one right now.

184
00:13:18,203 --> 00:13:24,428
This may come as a surprise, but it has only been 40
short years since humankind first learned how to fly.

185
00:13:25,168 --> 00:13:29,287
Until then, the skies were the exclusive
domain of demons and monsters.

186
00:13:29,311 --> 00:13:35,155
The flying magic you see us use today is actually
a demon spell mankind was able to repurpose.

187
00:13:35,235 --> 00:13:37,076
Nobody's looking for a lecture, okay?

188
00:13:37,296 --> 00:13:39,198
So can you make the
carriage levitate or not?

189
00:13:40,339 --> 00:13:44,802
We can't adapt their spell because we've merely
copied the how without understanding the why.

190
00:13:45,642 --> 00:13:48,944
Things larger than humans can
only be made to fly in short spurts.

191
00:13:49,164 --> 00:13:50,285
You should've led with that.

192
00:13:51,066 --> 00:13:52,407
We'll have to abandon ship.

193
00:13:53,243 --> 00:13:57,085
I'll fly out with our new merchant
ally, and Fern, you leave with Sein.

194
00:13:57,585 --> 00:13:58,585
Understood, ma'am.

195
00:13:58,925 --> 00:14:00,142
I'll get my cargo together.

196
00:14:00,166 --> 00:14:03,147
Uh, hey, uh, and me?

197
00:14:03,547 --> 00:14:05,028
I figured that you could jump down.

198
00:14:05,408 --> 00:14:06,488
What are you talking about?

199
00:14:07,129 --> 00:14:08,989
Pretty sure a fall like that would kill me.

200
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:11,430
Surely a warrior can
handle a fall from this height.

201
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:13,271
Don't look at me like I'm crazy!

202
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:15,751
You know good and well that
would snap every bone in my body!

203
00:14:15,852 --> 00:14:17,053
You really think it would?

204
00:14:17,873 --> 00:14:21,295
Eisen could free fall from any height
without getting so much as a scratch.

205
00:14:29,587 --> 00:14:30,884
What is wrong with this man?

206
00:14:30,908 --> 00:14:32,550
Heiter was appalled.

207
00:14:33,671 --> 00:14:37,394
Yet another story that goes to show
how far from normal Mr. Eisen is.

208
00:14:38,675 --> 00:14:43,219
Perhaps we can levitate the carriage for a
moment, just before it crashes into the forest.

209
00:14:43,679 --> 00:14:46,662
I'd need to calculate if I have
the power to stop a free fall.

210
00:14:47,423 --> 00:14:51,626
If I can't sufficiently reduce the force of
our plummet, we'd be ground into minced meat.

211
00:14:51,706 --> 00:14:53,548
Why'd you have to say it all scary-like?

212
00:14:54,527 --> 00:14:57,508
Whatever it is that we do,
we should probably do it quick.

213
00:14:58,328 --> 00:15:01,849
This type of monster kills its
prey by slamming it into the ground.

214
00:15:16,534 --> 00:15:18,675
Well, I suppose her idea is worth a shot.

215
00:15:21,099 --> 00:15:23,999
You better not drop us!

216
00:15:36,425 --> 00:15:37,425
We're alive!

217
00:15:37,805 --> 00:15:38,265
Indeed.

218
00:15:38,465 --> 00:15:40,166
Indicating our plan was a success.

219
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:41,726
You call that a success?

220
00:15:42,106 --> 00:15:43,666
What's worse is she called it a plan.

221
00:15:46,727 --> 00:15:49,428
Your horse was only slightly
injured, but I fixed it up for you.

222
00:15:49,928 --> 00:15:51,408
The greater concern is your carriage.

223
00:15:51,808 --> 00:15:52,948
It needs major repairs.

224
00:15:53,948 --> 00:15:54,948
Sorry.

225
00:15:55,049 --> 00:15:56,229
Please, don't apologize.

226
00:15:56,269 --> 00:15:56,869
I'm thankful.

227
00:15:57,109 --> 00:15:59,129
If it had just been me,
I would surely be dead.

228
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:01,910
It's gonna take some
time to fix the carriage.

229
00:16:17,366 --> 00:16:18,363
Huh?

230
00:16:18,387 --> 00:16:19,387
It should be right here.

231
00:16:21,028 --> 00:16:22,028
I wonder where it went.

232
00:16:25,891 --> 00:16:27,552
It's gotten a lot warmer lately.

233
00:16:28,472 --> 00:16:30,169
Might be time to start dressing lighter.

234
00:16:30,193 --> 00:16:34,836
Oh, by the way, Fern, about
that bracelet... Oh, right.

235
00:16:35,656 --> 00:16:37,978
This is what Mr. Stark
got me for my birthday.

236
00:16:38,698 --> 00:16:40,679
I spent three whole
hours picking out that thing.

237
00:16:41,419 --> 00:16:43,200
So you ended up being the one to choose?

238
00:16:43,621 --> 00:16:45,902
I wanted him to pick whatever
he thought would be best.

239
00:16:46,731 --> 00:16:49,193
Yeah, should've seen that coming.

240
00:16:49,913 --> 00:16:51,434
She put you through the ringer, huh?

241
00:16:52,054 --> 00:16:53,856
Her type is the hardest to deal with.

242
00:16:54,496 --> 00:16:55,496
Truth.

243
00:16:57,418 --> 00:16:58,418
What about this one?

244
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,981
Three hours of trying
to gauge her reactions.

245
00:17:02,881 --> 00:17:04,582
I felt like I was dying inside.

246
00:17:05,223 --> 00:17:06,059
You poor soul.

247
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:08,941
I can hear everything they're saying.

248
00:17:08,965 --> 00:17:10,146
Oh, well.

249
00:17:11,787 --> 00:17:13,768
It was all worth it since
she likes it so much.

250
00:17:19,452 --> 00:17:20,132
Attaboy.

251
00:17:20,393 --> 00:17:24,115
To tell you the truth, I didn't think you had
it in you to make such a romantic statement.

252
00:17:25,115 --> 00:17:26,856
That design is of a mirrored lotus.

253
00:17:27,276 --> 00:17:29,638
In the language of flowers,
it means eternal love.

254
00:17:30,138 --> 00:17:32,919
Around these parts, it's a
common symbol to give to a lover.

255
00:17:35,081 --> 00:17:36,081
Mr. Stark?

256
00:17:36,862 --> 00:17:38,002
I had no idea, okay?

257
00:17:38,202 --> 00:17:39,503
It's all a misunderstanding.

258
00:17:39,543 --> 00:17:42,103
You think I've got the first clue
about the language of flowers?

259
00:17:42,205 --> 00:17:43,205
No, of course not.

260
00:17:43,585 --> 00:17:44,326
You're an idiot.

261
00:17:44,546 --> 00:17:46,247
You're being even meaner than usual.

262
00:17:47,472 --> 00:17:49,554
Not like you're some flower genius either.

263
00:17:49,974 --> 00:17:51,095
What did you just say to me?

264
00:17:52,416 --> 00:17:53,416
Nothing, ma'am.

265
00:17:54,638 --> 00:17:57,320
So, uh, should I find
something to replace it?

266
00:17:58,340 --> 00:18:01,963
You put an incredible amount of effort
into picking out the perfect gift for me.

267
00:18:03,164 --> 00:18:04,621
Don't suggest such a thing again.

268
00:18:04,645 --> 00:18:06,887
I wouldn't dream of it.

269
00:18:13,192 --> 00:18:14,192
Something funny?

270
00:18:15,814 --> 00:18:16,955
No, not at all.

271
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:22,861
Mistress Frieren.

272
00:19:24,522 --> 00:19:26,124
We finished repairing the carriage.

273
00:19:26,724 --> 00:19:28,245
We'll depart early tomorrow morning.

274
00:19:29,487 --> 00:19:30,003
Understood.

275
00:19:30,027 --> 00:19:32,909
You've been sneaking away from us at night.

276
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:35,071
What is it that you're looking for?

277
00:19:36,172 --> 00:19:37,373
The ring Himmel gave me.

278
00:19:39,255 --> 00:19:40,255
Let me help.

279
00:19:40,876 --> 00:19:42,876
We'll wait to leave for
town until we've found it.

280
00:19:43,839 --> 00:19:44,839
That's all right.

281
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,762
If we don't have any luck
tonight, then I'll give up.

282
00:19:48,428 --> 00:19:49,989
I've grown used to losing things.

283
00:19:51,010 --> 00:19:53,833
Besides, that ring isn't all that
Himmel gave me over the years.

284
00:19:54,754 --> 00:19:55,350
The design.

285
00:19:55,374 --> 00:19:58,277
It has a mirrored lotus
like my bracelet does.

286
00:19:58,717 --> 00:20:01,019
In flower language,
that means eternal love.

287
00:20:02,380 --> 00:20:03,380
I didn't realize that.

288
00:20:05,002 --> 00:20:06,002
It doesn't matter.

289
00:20:06,364 --> 00:20:08,404
I seriously doubt Himmel
knew what it meant either.

290
00:20:09,726 --> 00:20:12,569
Regardless, I'm certain it's important.

291
00:20:13,810 --> 00:20:14,931
Let's look for it together.

292
00:20:18,620 --> 00:20:20,141
I wish you would have told me sooner.

293
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:26,207
Given my line of work, I'm typically the first stop
when folks in my village lose valuable jewelry.

294
00:20:27,087 --> 00:20:29,149
This is a spell for
finding lost accessories.

295
00:20:29,970 --> 00:20:33,893
I was intending to give it to you as a reward for
all your assistance with my carriage and horse.

296
00:20:56,176 --> 00:20:57,296
Frieren.

297
00:20:58,170 --> 00:21:03,240
To say a special thanks for all your hard work on
that side quest, please choose whatever you'd like.

298
00:21:03,840 --> 00:21:04,840
Jewelry, huh?

299
00:21:06,301 --> 00:21:10,459
I would have preferred something
from a magic shop, but this one will do.

300
00:21:10,483 --> 00:21:11,724
That was too easy.

301
00:21:12,024 --> 00:21:13,664
You should put some more thought into it.

302
00:21:17,110 --> 00:21:18,471
What's wrong?

303
00:21:19,912 --> 00:21:20,953
Nothing.

304
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:42,734
Frieren.

305
00:21:43,450 --> 00:21:44,331
Ah, yes.

306
00:22:22,599 --> 00:22:24,400
You were close to giving up your search.

307
00:22:25,060 --> 00:22:26,060
Glad you didn't?

308
00:22:33,782 --> 00:22:34,782
Maybe I am.

309
00:22:38,805 --> 00:22:42,828
I meant to ask, why exactly are
you wearing a mirrored lotus bracelet?

310
00:22:43,409 --> 00:22:45,411
Because Mr. Stark is an idiot.

311
00:22:46,572 --> 00:22:47,572
No respect.

